## Setting up a data schema
A data schema is set up using the panel provided.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Editing the data schema
- Using a suitable text or XML file editor, open the file containing the data schema.

- Select all the contents and copy them to the clipboard.

- Click the **Change **button in the **Change data schema **panel.

- In the **Paste configuration from XML **window, paste the contents of the notes into the text area.

![](data:image/png;base64,) 

- Click **Apply **to confirm and close the window.

> Warning

If Document Composition is unable to process the data schema entered, an error will be generated and the application will have to be restarted.

## Replacing the attributes inside the data schema
The **Assisted Replacement **will replace all usages of a given attribute or data section with another attribute or data section: this means that if you are currently using /*File/DOCUMENT/TEMPLATE/@name *in 100 resources within the project and want to change it to */FILE/DOCUMENT/TEMPLATE/USER/@firstName*, the product will make the 100 replacements for you.

The feature can be used in two ways:

- manually replacing the attributes

- using a prepared XML-file containing descriptions how the XML-structure must be changed

### Manually replacing the attributes inside the data schema
- Click **Assisted replace **in the **Change data schema **panel. The following window is displayed:

![](data:image/png;base64,) 

- From the **Source **list, select the attribute that must be replaced. The selected attribute is highlighted in yellow.

- From the **Substitute **list, select the attribute that will be used to replace the current one.

- Click **New replacement**. The attribute to be replaced will be listed in the **Replacements **table.

> Warning

The following operation is irreversible. Once you click Apply, the system performs all the substitutions.

- Click **Apply **to perform the desired substitutions.

> Note

Attribute styles are variations of the attributes that you can use for variable data substitution in text content. For example, you can create a style which applies financial formatting to a numeric value. When you attach an attribute to your resources, you can either use the default attribute or one of its styles. You can create styles in the Data view by selecting attributes and using the panel on the right hand side.

### Replacing the attributes by pasting an XML replacement list
- Open the **XML **Tab. The following panel is displayed:

![](data:image/png;base64,) 

- Click **Import**. The file browse windows open allowing you to select the replacement file.

- Select the XML file with the instructions to use.

**Example of typical XML file for replacement**

`&lt;?xml versionz"1.0" encodingz"UTF-8"?&gt;
&lt;REPLACEMENTS&gt;
 &lt;REPLACEMENT mode="attributeToAttribute"
source="/FILE/DOCUMENT/TEMPLATE/@sourceT"
replacement="/FILE/DOCUMENT/TEMPLATE/@repIT"/&gt;
 
 &lt;REPLACEMENT mode="datasection"
source="/FILE/DOCUMENT/TEMPLATE/H1"
replacement="/FILE/DOCUMENT/TEMPLATE/H1/H2"/&gt;
 
 &lt;REPLACEMENT mode="attributeToStyle"
source="/FILE/DOCUMENT/TEMPLATE/RIEPILOGO_IVANOCE_IVA_SINGOLA/@sourceAS"
replacement="[118028_REPLASSTILE]"/&gt;
 
 &lt;REPLACEMENT mode="attributeToAttribute"
source="/FILE/DOCUMENT/TEMPLATE/RIEPILOGO_IVA/VOCE_IVA_SINGOLA/@sourceAA"
replacement="/FILE/DOCUMENT/TEMPLATE/RIEPILOGO_IVANOCE_IVA_DOPPIA/@replAA"/&gt;
 
 &lt;REPLACEMENT mode="styleToAttribute"
source="[118019_SRCSTILE]"
replacement="/FILE/DOCUMENT/TEMPLATE/RIEPILOGO_IVANOCE_IVA_DOPPIA/@replSA"/&gt;
 
 &lt;REPLACEMENT mode="styleToStyle"
source="[118021_SOURCESSSTILE]"
replacement="[18031_REPLSSSTILE]"/&gt;
 
 &lt;REPLACEMENT mode="datasection"
source="/FILE/DOCUMENT/TEMPLATE/H1/H2"
replacement="/FILE/DOCUMENT/TEMPLATE/H1/H2/H3"/&gt;
&lt;/REPLACEMENTS&gt;`> Note

This feature allows to replace all occurrences of a given attribute, attribute skin or datasection with another attribute, skin or datasection. The data schema is not changed by this operation. Bindings, rule sets and contents may be changed.

The XML instructions are a set of REPLACEMENT elements with a source and replacement fields that depend on the operation. The allowed operation types are listed in the following table:

Mode

Description

**attributeToStyle**

Replace the default style of an attribute with another attribute style.

**attributeToAttribute**

Replace individual attributes in rules and contents.

**datasection**

Look for datasections within bindings and replace them.

**styleToAttribute**

Replace every occurrence of a given style with the default style of another attribute.

**styleToStyle**

Replace every occurrence of a given style with another style.

> ## **Tips on restructuring the entire contract file**
In order to apply changes to your contract file:

- Edit the contract file by adding the datasections and attributes you wish to point to. Do not remove the old datasections and attributes at this time.

- Import the contract file.

- Run assisted replacement and create a replacement link for every attribute you wish to move.

- Run a preview to check everything is fine.

- Delete the old datasection and attributes from the contract file. They are not necessary anymore.
